- Vercel project: [FILL IN]
- Supabase project: [FILL IN]
- Key env vars: [FILL IN e.g. MOBIUS_SUPABASE_URL, MOBIUS_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY, API keys]

## Current focus
The main active task is refactoring the `index.html` file. Existing code sections are being systematically extracted into new, dedicated ES module JavaScript files within the `app/js/` directory, aiming to reduce `index.html` to a minimal shell.

## Key constraints
- North direction is consistently mapped to the negative Z-axis in Three.js.
- Microsoft Edge is the mandatory development browser due to Chrome compatibility issues.
- The "Touch it, extract it" rule: any code touched in `index.html` must be moved to a separate ES module in `app/js/`.
- Code must be robust, modular, and maintainable; short-term patches are forbidden.
- Third-party libraries in the `lib/` folder must not be modified.
- Chromium-only browser APIs are permitted.

